headline: I.C.E
summary: Perform enforcement duties that include the apprehension, processing, detention and deportation of illegal or criminal aliens. We work in any one of our technical, professional, administrative, or management occupations directly supporting our law enforcement mission.

positions.description: U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE), the largest investigative agency in the Department of Homeland Security, is responsible for enforcing the nation's immigration and customs laws.Â
